place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: People here are great and timely. was help out by courtnie and even tho she seemed new was very helpful. thank you guys for getting me to work on time unlike dunkin.
Just waited ten minutes for a water  it wasn't even busy I hate this Starbucks so much

Always clean, great service

I recently stopped by the is Starbucks located near Piper Glen in Rea Rd. This location has been here for many years so they obviously are doing something right. I found the store to be very clean, well stocked and the atmosphere was welcoming.

The customer service is very good, the associates are very knowledgeable and helpful. My order was taken quickly and the wait time wasn't bad but I noticed that a line quickly formed after I ordered and there was only one associate to do all the work.

She worked as efficiently as she could and got the rest of the orders taken care of. There are plenty of seating areas here, indoors and outdoors. However, some of the areas aren't clean and that may be because they were short staffed.
Overall, I had a good expert but it could've been better.

Diana is the best.
I stop by here once a week when I shop at Trader Joes.
When she gets my mobile
order, she always asks me if I want more form or milk. I can tell she really cares about customers what they want. I would love to order here as long as she works here.
Very high prices compared to local

I usually order ahead and pick up my drink, but the app was down a few days ago and I ordered in the restaurant. While making my drink the barista held my cup up under her nose and started breathing in the smell.  I won't be going back to this location.

I ordered something as simple as a Carmel macchiato! It taste bitter and only 1/3 of a cup on the go! STAY CLEAR OF THIS LOCATION! This is the second or 3rd time they have done this.Too bad the coffee does not match with the atmosphere! I expected better. Called the location to put in a complaint no one picks up the phone.

The place was conveniently located by the library and four mile creek park before you get to I485.
They have very nice large capacity outdoor patio (good pleasant surprise). Its great add on to the place by the park.

There was only one barista when we made our order and she was able to manage until more people joined her. Right about hour to close there was good traffic and she was able to handle it.

Our drinks were good and timely. Thanks
dog friendly!

The Baristas here are friendly and energetic! I've been to many Starbucks locations, but the staff here is wonderful!
Excellent customer service.  Clean and well maintained.
Polite staff. Nice to interact with. Made our experience enjoyable

Usual Starbucks standard taste and ambience.

Love this location. I come to this starbucks every Tuesday morning. The staff are always so pleasant and their service is amazing. I have been here during the day too and the service was still outstanding even when it's super busy. They are always smiling and gettinf a coffee here is a great way to start your day!
Nice outdoor patio.  I was able to sit outside talking with a friend enjoying my tea and oatmeal - first time in 14 months.
Always my favorite place and for my family.
I like it's Iced coffee!

Thank you to the wonderful staff here that always does a wonderful job making my drinks to perfection. Special shout to Josh for putting a twist on my iced white mocha and adding pumps of vanilla with blonde expresso.

Nice small location. They don't have indoor seating but there are several tables outside. Masks are required. Safety dividers at register. For me it's a nice place to get my caffeine fix before or after walk on a Greenway across the street.
drink is ordered on time mobile or in store but due to the covid-19 the stores temporarily close right now and it's been closed since last night around 4:00 yesterday afternoon they shut down

First of all, thank you Adrienne and Christina (sorry if I misspelled) for your carefully following the governor's guidance regarding COVID-19. I have been elsewhere (ahem, the phone center at my local Target...) where people seem to think I am hard of hearing for whatever reason and lower their masks to speak with me.

My friend was treating me to coffee. I casually mentioned looking at the menu that the lime drink sounded pretty cool. I guess as new customers (and coming in all sweaty from a long bike ride) we got a double-treat; I got a couple of samples of the fruit drinks and he got one, too (lined up here to show off the rainbow cornucopia)! Strong customer service and friendly folks.

Been coming here for years, and by far the best Starbucks around to come and relax with a good book. The staff and management have always been on point, very caring and mindful. Incredible atmosphere and community!!
Nice and fresh coffee
I meet at this Starbucks every Saturday with a walk/run group. They expediate, accommodate, and tolerate us.

Great social spot. Decent coffee. Stop in on any given Saturday morning for a nitro coffee or a espresso drink. Large morning running crowd welcoming anyone for some conversation. One of the best Carmel frappachinos I have had yet! Delish!! Nice place to sit and catch up with a friend as well.

Love it.. it is star bucks$$$ of course.. but the coffe is awesome.. i like the way they keep changing the character of the coffee.. love their anniversary blend, antigua, ans casi cielo.. dark roasts have a different flavour..love this after my runs. Start my morning with their coffee..

Good community-friendly Starbucks. I'm there most Saturday mornings with a bunch of other runners and F3 guys. The staff is very friendly and even puts out cups of ice water for the runners coming back from a run. Mobile order through app if you can - the line can get pretty long.

I have a coffee that is involved, and when I'm not at my starbucks I am very careful to slow my order down and I ask the person to repeat it back, nicely explains along the order that it is often made incorrectly. Went to PGSB not mine but 2-3 a month I head in there. Being a person who has gone to starbucks for 20 some years you can spot the new or clueless person,  so I repeated my order 3 times, and I asked to see the cup he said it's fine. So I did 4 checks I get over to p/u and my coffee is wrong! What a shock! I've got a fever, and I try to not come off as the crazy cat lady, I ask what this order is and she says things back I have never requested, I said NO and repeated the order again, and she say 2 different times is this it? It's like no stop make the coffee correct and I'll get out of your business, easy! Then rather than look me in the eye and apologize she looks down a and puts my coffee on the counter so I have to move to get it, I'm right next to her, that would have had her look at me!

It's now almost an hour and a half before close, and the staff are using a very loud vacuum to clean up the pastry case. Soon they'll probably start asking me to move my stuff so they can mop. This seems to be a theme at many Starbucks I've visited -- get your clean up done, well in advance of close, regardless of how noxious it might be for customers. They close at 9, so kiss your ambience goodbye at around 7:30.

I like the interior configuration of the store.  Some good tables and chairs.  Not huge though, if that is what you are looking for.  Very nice porch area.  Nearby trees bearing white flowers in spring.

WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE EXPERIENCE I HAVE EVER RECEIVED!!!!!  I brought my less than two pounds, 4 month old Chihuahua into store in my pocket because it was cold and rainy and living close  to this Starbucks, my car was not warm.  I was leaving town early and wanted coffee.  Cashier looked at me when I enter store, I was in line for approximately 5 minutes as cashier fumbled around with 2 prior customers.  When I got to register, I ordered to go drink and cashier immediately after swiping my card told me I needed to leave store because they did not allow pets, I said I was sorry, and he indicated that he would deliver my drink to my car.  As I see approximately 10 customers go in and come out over the period of 10 minutes, no drink was delivered.  I had to go back into store, now no one in line to see the cashier doing nothing and my coffee sitting on the stand.  WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE EVER, I EXPECT STARBUCKS AND OTHER COMPANIES I PARTONIZE TO FOLLOW THROUGH WITH WHAT THEY SAY THEY ARE GOING TO DO.  I will NEVER visit this Starbucks again, I will call the main Starbucks customer service hotline to explain situation and I will possibly boycott Starbucks completely in the future. Caribou Coffee has won my business in the Charlotte area and has never complained about my pet on to go order.

Seeing the interactions of this cashier with 2 previous customers and my interaction, this cashier needs to be fired.
